comment: A named lemma of Sylow's second and third theorems. If ` G ` is a finite ` P ` -group that acts on the finite set ` Y ` , then the set ` Z ` of all points of ` Y ` fixed by every element of ` G ` has cardinality equivalent to the cardinality of ` Y ` , ` mod P ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 17-Jan-2015.)
